1:01:34.073 --> 1:01:37.943
And, Jim, I want to thank you very much 
for all your help with this program. 


1:01:37.943 --> 1:01:40.480
I really, really appreciate it. 


1:01:40.480 --> 1:01:42.515
Now, before we conclude, 


1:01:42.515 --> 1:01:45.852
we’d like to visit the city of Cuzco in Peru, 


1:01:45.852 --> 1:01:50.890
where we have 
a Remote Translation Office, or RTO.


1:01:50.890 --> 1:01:54.000
The city of Cuzco is a stopover 
for travelers to Machu Picchu, 


1:01:55.795 --> 1:01:59.932
a historic sanctuary 
of the former Inca Empire, 


1:01:59.932 --> 1:02:02.435
located high up in the mountains. 


1:02:02.435 --> 1:02:06.272
Machu Picchu is an architectural marvel. 


1:02:06.272 --> 1:02:09.442
The design is earthquake resistant. 


1:02:09.442 --> 1:02:12.379
Giant stones were cut so precisely 


1:02:12.378 --> 1:02:15.581
that in many places a piece of paper 


1:02:15.582 --> 1:02:18.084
cannot fit in between them. 


1:02:18.083 --> 1:02:21.586
At such high altitudes, 
you can also see llamas, 


1:02:21.587 --> 1:02:24.890
which are raised 
in the Andes Mountains. 


1:02:24.890 --> 1:02:27.127
The Inca people spoke Quechua, 


1:02:27.127 --> 1:02:29.129
a language that is spoken 


1:02:29.128 --> 1:02:32.063
by millions of Peruvians today.


1:02:32.063 --> 1:02:35.000
There has been a translation office in Cuzco 


1:02:35.000 --> 1:02:37.303
since 2004, 


1:02:37.303 --> 1:02:39.305
but as the work grew, 


1:02:39.305 --> 1:02:41.807
so did the need for more office space. 


1:02:41.807 --> 1:02:46.812
So in 2016, a new RTO was dedicated. 


1:02:46.812 --> 1:02:50.884
The blessings of the translation work 
have been evident. 


1:02:50.883 --> 1:02:55.521
Since the Bible Teach book 
was released in Quechua in 2007, 


1:02:55.522 --> 1:02:57.857
the number of publishers increased 


1:02:57.857 --> 1:03:00.125
from about 700 


1:03:00.125 --> 1:03:04.163
to nearly 1,700 last year. 


1:03:04.163 --> 1:03:06.098
In addition to The Watchtower 


1:03:06.098 --> 1:03:08.100
and the Life and Ministry Meeting Workbook, 


1:03:08.100 --> 1:03:11.637
videos are translated at this office, 


1:03:11.637 --> 1:03:15.709
ranging from JW Broadcasting 
monthly programs 


1:03:15.708 --> 1:03:19.845
to episodes of Become Jehovah’s Friend.


1:03:19.845 --> 1:03:23.482
There are several regions in Peru 
where Quechua is spoken, 


1:03:23.482 --> 1:03:27.052
all with slightly different dialects 
and expressions. 


1:03:27.052 --> 1:03:30.289
Hence, 
each translation team 


1:03:30.288 --> 1:03:33.926
has representatives from these areas 


1:03:33.927 --> 1:03:36.062
in order to ensure that the translation 


1:03:36.062 --> 1:03:38.430
is universally understood 


1:03:38.430 --> 1:03:40.500
among Quechua speakers. 


1:03:40.500 --> 1:03:45.203
Approximately 40 brothers 
and sisters work at the RTO, 


1:03:45.203 --> 1:03:48.573
of which 15 are full-time. 


1:03:48.573 --> 1:03:50.676
In the Cuzco area, 


1:03:50.677 --> 1:03:54.647
there are 28 congregations and 38 groups, 


1:03:54.647 --> 1:03:58.150
with about 2,000 publishers.


1:03:58.150 --> 1:04:02.053
We love our brothers and sisters 
in Cuzco very much indeed. 


1:04:02.053 --> 1:04:03.621
And they want you to know 


1:04:03.622 --> 1:04:05.625
how much they love you. 


1:04:05.625 --> 1:04:07.793
Well, until next time, 


1:04:07.793 --> 1:04:10.630
this is JW Broadcasting 


1:04:10.630 --> 1:04:21.323
from the world headquarters 
of Jehovah’s Witnesses.

